userReviews: Delicious authentic food. Great green curry, appetizers and guava cocktail.
Everything here is amazing!  Chef Cho is incredible!
Phad Thai made from glass noodles and with only a few sprouts?  No thank you, I'm not interested to investigate the menu further.
Crab fried rice is bad-ass. Comparable to if not better than Osha.
Green curry roti. Pineapple fried rice. Red curry.
Pumpkin Curry is unique, but other stuff looks good too.
The pad see ew is awesome!! Hope I spelled that right. Get everything with Thai iced tea to cool down the spicy!
Pumpkin curry and coconut rice. This will be the best party in your mouth, ever!!
Tasty food. Nice service. They have good bunch of vegetarian option .. Must try: young coconut water, crispy rolls, roti with eggplant gravy n cucumber peanut salad .. Good place to go on a date ;)
Do not miss the crab fried rice. So good!!
We went there on a Saturday night and the service was a bit slower than average. 10 mins to get water, 30 mins for the food.

userReviews: Tom yum soup needs a lot of works and improvement
My favorite place for lunch! Great food, service, and prices!  I come here with my coworkers so often they know all of our orders and always have a table ready when we arrive.
Solid pad see ew and Penang curry.
Not a very Thai thing to get, but I love their standard fried rice (Kaw Pad). Could be the butter and butter. And their Thai teas are bottomless!
BBQ pork with white rice,  just dump it on your rice with the sweet and sour sauce, delicious! I got so full, and I still had leftovers! Great curry too!
If you would like to pay with MasterCard take a look at the notice in receipt - there is unusual USD to EUR conversion procedure with >3% conversion fee. I refused to go with it.

love the pad thai chicken and thai iced tea :)
